   <text type="translation">
      <body>
         <pb facs="1864_07_09_Kniffler_Nagasaki_von_Johann_Lange_Sohns_Wwe_Co_Bremen_1.tif" n="envelope"/>
         <p>&gt;SHANGHAI<lb/>10<lb/>[...]<lb/>BAU
                FRANCAIS<lb/>SHANGHAI<lb/>28<lb/>AOUT<lb/>6[...]<lb/>via Marseille
                <lb/>BREMEN.TH.&amp;TX.<lb/>25<lb/>8<lb/>5-6 N<lb/>Messrs. L. Kniffler
                +Co<lb/>TOURS<lb/>27<lb/>AOUT<lb/>64<lb/>[...] P.P.<lb/>⟨paid⟩
                <lb/>Nagasaki<lb/>Japan<lb/>⟨1864<lb/>Bremen 25th August<lb/>Joh: Lange Sohn's Ww
                +Co<lb/>R[eceived] 17th Oct.<lb/>22nd Oct⟩</p>
         <pb facs="1864_07_09_Kniffler_Nagasaki_von_Johann_Lange_Sohns_Wwe_Co_Bremen_2.tif" n="2"/>
         <p>Copy<lb/> Bremen 9th July 1864<lb/> JOH. LANGE SOHNS WWE &amp; CO<lb/>BREMEN <lb/>
                Messrs. L. Kniffler + Co<lb/>Nagasaki<lb/>Above you will find a copy of our
                respectful letter from <lb/>25th of last month &amp; we have not since had the
                pleasure of<lb/>hearing from you. <lb/>It would please us very much to be informed
                as soon as possible<lb/>about the sale of our guns so that this business can
                finally<lb/>be laid to rest. <lb/>Since our last letter, tea has become
                significantly more sluggish &amp; <lb/>the prices for Japanese types at least ½ -1°
                lower. The<lb/>demand for America has come to a total halt for the
                momentarily.<lb/>Camphor quiet without change, 95 - 100 / ; here 20 gt. are
                <lb/>being offered for Chin. wares, <lb/>fish oil is sluggish; nominal value £ 38 ½
                p ton,<lb/>tobacco worth 8[?]½ - 9 gt., wax 13 - 15 gt., galls 22 rh,<lb/>your Mr.
                Gildemeister is present here again at the <lb/>moment. <lb/>We are looking forward
                to further news from you &amp;<lb/>sign off in devoted friendship<lb/>Yours<lb/>the
                25th Aug 1864<lb/>We last wrote to you on the 9th of last month<lb/>+ have since had
                the pleasure of receiving your<lb/>welcome letter from 6th June, in the answer to
                which </p>
         <pb facs="1864_07_09_Kniffler_Nagasaki_von_Johann_Lange_Sohns_Wwe_Co_Bremen_3.tif" n="3"/>
         <p>we thank you for your reports. <lb/>We have little news to tell you from here, too,
                <lb/>about Japanese products; there is very little<lb/>demand for tea because the
                export to America <lb/>has stopped in its entirety following the <lb/>significant
                increase in customs duty; we hear that<lb/>the buyer of our 132 boxes on the Dunmore
                <lb/>ended up doing very poor business for just this <lb/>reason + we therefore
                regret not having used<lb/>the previous[?] demand to sell. <lb/>Should you decide to
                undertake some<lb/>shipments on shared account, we hope <lb/>that it will be at
                quite cheap prices. <lb/>Tobacco remains unchanged here &amp; your <lb/>latest
                prices are definitely too high. <lb/>Camphor remains sluggish at 92/6 +[?]; due
                to<lb/>this price, purchases seem to us to pose <lb/>little risk [?] &amp; will you
                please keep an eye <lb/>on this article. <lb/>Galls are worth 22 rh, but this price
                will <lb/>hardly last once larger shipments arrive. <lb/>Veget. wax 13 - 15
                gt.,<lb/>from Yokohama some lots of tea <lb/>arrived recently, which promptly found
                <lb/>buyers because of its nice quality: </p>
         <table>
            <row>
               <cell>58/8</cell>
               <cell>boxes</cell>
               <cell>Young Haysan</cell>
               <cell>at 42 gt</cell>
            </row>
            <row>
               <cell>16/8</cell>
               <cell>"</cell>
               <cell>Haysan</cell>
               <cell>" 44 gt</cell>
            </row>
            <row>
               <cell>6/8</cell>
               <cell>"</cell>
               <cell>Gunpowder</cell>
               <cell>" 31 gt</cell>
            </row>
         </table>
         <pb facs="1864_07_09_Kniffler_Nagasaki_von_Johann_Lange_Sohns_Wwe_Co_Bremen_4.tif" n="4"/>
         <p>We are looking forward to your letters about <lb/>our guns, which you have hopefully
                sold now, <lb/>and sign<lb/>respectfully<lb/>Joh. Lange Sohn’s Wwe + Co.</p>
      </body>
